weather.text: ay : Mostly sunny and cool, with a high of 68 degrees. Winds SSW at 5-10 mph.  Friday : Mostly cloudy and cool, with late-morning thunderstorms. Temperatures reached 71. Winds SW at 10-15 mph. Rainfall totaled .05 inches. Second-round play was suspended at 10:51 a.m. due to a dangerous weather situation. Play resumed at 12:12 p.m.—a 1-hour, 21-minute delay. The afternoon wave was delayed 1 hour, 20 minutes with the first time being 1:30 p.m.  Saturday : Dense morning fog forced a 90-minute delay to the start of the third round with sunny skies the rest of the day. High of 77. Morning winds N at 4-8 mph shifting to SW at 5-10 mph in the afternoon.  Sunday : Partly cloudy, with temperatures reaching 80. Winds W at 8-12 mph.

notes:
The 2011 Wells Fargo Championship winner Lucas Glover (67-68-69-69)became the first player in the nine-year history of the Wells Fargo Championship to record all four rounds in the 60s.   
   
 Former Clemson Tiger teammates Lucas Glover and Jonathan Byrd finished regulation deadlocked at the 2011 Wells Fargo Championship at 15-under 273, with Glover converting a par on the first extra hole(par-4 18th)for the victory. The playoff was the fourth in the tournament's nine-year history.   
   
 Five of the nine winners of the Wells Fargo Championship— David Toms (2003), Vijay Singh (2005), Jim Furyk (2006), Tiger Woods (2007)and Lucas Glover (2011)—have captured major championships.   
   
   Lucas Glover led the 2011 Wells Fargo Championship field in Strokes Gained-Putting at 2.651 strokes per round.   
   
   Lucas Glover's opening-round 67 in 2011 is the lowest start by a winner of the Wells Fargo Championship. His 72-hole total of 15-under-par 273 is one shy of the tournament record held by 2008 champion Anthony Kim.   
   
   Lucas Glover made his eighth start at the Wells Fargo Championship in 2011, a venue where he has enjoyed considerable success over the years. He has missed just one cut(2005)and amassed four top-10 finishes, highlighted by his win in 2011 and a tie for second in 2009.   
   
 In memory of Seve Ballesteros, who passed away due to complications from brain cancer on May 7, play was suspended play during the final round(May 8)of the 2011 Wells Fargo Championship for a one-minute moment of silence at 3:08 p.m. EDT.   
   
   Phil Mickelson tied for ninth in his eighth career start at the 2011 Wells Fargo Championship. The lefthander owns the most top-10 finishes at the event with six(tied for fifth in 2004, tied for seventh in 2005, tied for third in 2007, tied for fourth in 2009, second in 2010 and tied for ninth in 2011).   
   
   Pat Perez's 12-under 132 in 2011 set the Wells Fargo Championship tournament record for lowest first 36-hole score. The previous low was posted by Bill Haas (2011)and Bo Van Pelt (2006)at 10-under 134.
